S"{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2014}}\n{{Infobox congressman\n| name        = John Katko\n| image       = \n| imagesize   = \n| state       = [[New York]]\n| office      = Member-elect of the<br>[[U.S. House of Representatives]]<br>from [[New York's 24th congressional district|New York's 24th district]]\n| term_start  = January 3, 2015\n| term_end    =\n| succeeding  = [[Dan Maffei]]\n| succeeded   = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1962|11|9}}\n| birth_place = [[Syracuse, New York]], U.S.\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| birthname   = John Michael Katko\n| nationality = [[United States|American]]\n| party       = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| residence   = [[Camillus, New York]], U.S.\n| alma_mater  = [[Niagara University]]<br>[[Syracuse University]]\n| occupation  = Assistant U.S. Attorney}}\n\n'''John Michael Katko''' (born November 9, 1962) is an American politician who was elected to serve [[New York's 24th congressional district|New York's 24th district]] in the [[United States House of Representatives elections, 2014]]. He will take office on January 3, 2015.\n\n==Career==\nKatko is a former federal prosecutor. He attended [[Niagara University]] where he earned a bachelor of arts degree in political science, and the [[Syracuse University College of Law]] where he earned a [[juris doctorate]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/152546/john-katko#.VFmu2_TF_Zk|title=Project Vote Smart - The Voter's Self Defense System|work=Project Vote Smart|accessdate=November 5, 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe ran against [[Dan Maffei]] in the [[United States House of Representatives elections, 2014]] and was declared the winner on November 4, 2014 by 20 percentage points--the largest margin of defeat suffered by an incumbent in the cycle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syracuse.com/news/index.ssf/2014/11/john_katko_declared_winner_over_rep_dan_maffei_in_race_for_congress.html|title=John Katko declared winner over Rep. Dan Maffei in race for Congress|work=syracuse.com|accessdate=November 5, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nKatko was born in Syracuse in 1962, and is a graduate of [[Bishop Ludden Junior/Senior High School|Bishop Ludden High School]].<ref>[http://www.nationaljournal.com/article/535254 Profile], nationaljournal.com; accessed November 10, 2014.</ref> \n\nKatko was raised in suburban [[Camillus, New York]], where he now resides with his wife, Robin Katko and their sons: Sean, Liam & Logan.<ref name=meet>{{cite web|url=http://www.syracuse.com/news/index.ssf/2014/10/john_katko_gang_prosecutor_thrives_on_chaos_competition_wants_to_go_to_congress.html|title=Meet John Katko: Career gang prosecutor talks of taking on 'knuckleheads' in Congress|work=syracuse.com|accessdate=November 5, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.johnkatkoforcongress.com 2014 campaign website]\n\n<!--{{S-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{USRepSuccessionBox |\n  state=New York|\n  district=24 |\n  before=[[Dan Maffei]] |\n  start=January 3, 2015\n}}\n{{S-end}}-->\n{{Persondata <!-- Metadata: see [[Wikipedia:Persondata]]. -->\n| NAME              = Katko, John Michael\n| ALTERNATIVE NAMES =\n| SHORT DESCRIPTION = American politician\n| DATE OF BIRTH     = November 9, 1962\n| PLACE OF BIRTH    = Syracuse, New York, U.S.\n| DATE OF DEATH     =\n| PLACE OF DEATH    =\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Katko, John}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Camillus, New York]]\n[[Category:Niagara University alumni]]\n[[Category:Syracuse University College of Law alumni]]\n[[Category:New York Republicans]]\n[[Category:People from Syracuse, New York]]\n[[Category:Republican Party members of the United States House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Members of the United States House of Representatives from New York]]"
